-- Irish Minister Says Complacency Is Biggest Danger to Yes Vote
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-03-18T13:31:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/irish-minister-says-complacency-is-biggest-danger-to-yes-vote.html
Ireland’s European Affairs Minister
Lucinda Creighton said complacency is the biggest threat to a
yes vote in Ireland’s referendum on the European Fiscal Compact.  The result isn’t a foregone conclusion and those supporting
a yes vote shouldn’t be lulled into inactivity by opinion polls
that indicate the referendum will probably go in their favor,
Creighton wrote in a column in Dublin’s  Sunday Business Post .  To contact the reporter on this story:
